  "text": "There is a more radical alternative view. If systematic open enquiry is the contemporary guarantor of robust and stable social knowledge within a plethora of easily accessible opinion [CITATION_1] , it can be argued that engaging in research to help generate such knowledge is a social duty rather than something from which to be protected [CITATION_2] . It follows that it would be a professional duty",
